Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[kə'rɔbəri]
*danh từ
 ■điệu múa corrobori (một điệu múa dân gian ở Uc)
*nội động từ
 ■nhảy múa theo điệu corrobori

Anh - Anh
corroboree
[kə'rɒbəri]
■ noun an Australian Aboriginal dance ceremony in the form of a sacred ritual or informal gathering.
Origin
from Dharuk garaabara, denoting a style of dancing.

sentences.en: The sled was going so fast it couldn't be stopped. There wasn' t time to turn it. The sled went right under the hog and picked him up. With a squeal he sat down on James, and he kept on squealing, long and loud and shrill,'Squee - eeee - ee - ee! Squee - ee - ee - ee - ee - ee!'
